Class EntityManager<E,​ID>

  • java.lang.Object
    • proj.w41k4z.orm.spec.EntityManager<E,​ID>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataAccessObject<E,​ID>
    public class EntityManager<E,​ID>
extends Object
implements DataAccessObject<E,​ID>
    The EntityManager is used to manage entity persistence and transactions. For a general usage, do not specify the Entity type and the ID type, use Object instead. Like this: 
     
 EntityManager<Object, Object> entityManager = new EntityManager<>();
